    <text n="1" corresp="#PL1F1" xml:lang="emodeng">
        <body>
            <div n="1" type="plate" facs="../images/Derricke_EUL_first_edition/EUL_plate01.tif">
                <div type="frontMatter" corresp="#PL1F1_frontMatter">
                    <div type="title" corresp="#PL1F1_title">
                        <head><hi rend="roman">A NOTABLE DISCOvery most lively describing the state and condition of the <orgName corresp="#Woodkern">Wild men in <placeName corresp="#Ireland">Ireland</placeName></orgName>, properly called <orgName corresp="#Woodkern">Woodkern</orgName>, with their actions, and exercises wherein they are daily occupied, also the order of their rebellion and success of the same is likewise detected. Which also concludeth with the coming in of <seg rend="italics"><persName corresp="#TONeill">Turlough Luineach</persName></seg> the great O’<seg rend="smallcaps">Neill</seg> of <placeName corresp="#Ireland">Ireland</placeName>, submitting himself to the right honorable <persName corresp="#HSidney">Sir <seg rend="italics">Henry Sidney</seg></persName>, at what time he was L. Deputy general there of the said Land, being in <seg rend="italics">An. <date calendar="julien" when="1578">1578</date></seg>. Now published and set forth by <seg rend="italics"><persName corresp="#JDerrick">JOHN DERRICK</persName></seg> this present year of our Lord. <date calendar="julien" when="1581">1581</date>. For pleasure and delight of those, whose mindes in laudable exercises are virtuously occupied.</hi></head>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div type="rights" corresp="#PL1F1_rights">
                        <p xml:id="PL1F1_permission"><seg rend="italics">Seen and allowed.</seg></p><note corresp="#PL1F1_permission" place="end" type="editorial" n="1" resp="#ASilva">This line acts as an indicator Permission to print and distribute.</note>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div type="imprint" corresp="#PL1F1_imprint">
                        <p><metamark place="margin" corresp="#PL1F1_pilcrow"/><g ref="#pilcrow">¶</g> At <placeName corresp="#London">London</placeName>, printed by <persName corresp="#JDay">John Day</persName> dwelling over <placeName corresp="#Aldersgate">Aldersgate</placeName> <date when="1581" calendar="julien">1581</date>.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div corresp="#PL1F1_titleDecor">
                        <figure>
                            <figDesc>ADD YOUR DESCRIPTION OF THIS DECORATIVE ELEMENT</figDesc>
                            <!-- ADD YOUR DESCRIPTION -->
                        </figure>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="woodcut" corresp="#PL1F1_woodcut">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc corresp="./plateNotes.xml#PL1F1_plateDesc"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
                <div type="descriptiveText" corresp="#PL1F1_descriptiveText" rend="blackletter">
                    
                    
                    <div type="column" n="1" corresp="#PL1F1_column1">
                        <cb n="1"/>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="AA">
                            <l n="1">The lively shape of <orgName corresp="#Woodkern">Irish <hi rend="roman">kern</hi></orgName>, most perfect to behold,</l>
                            <anchor type="caption" corresp="#PL1F1_caption_A" xml:id="PL1F1_capA_text" sameAs="#PL1F1_woodcutZone_A"/><metamark place="margin" function="imageCaptionLink" corresp="#PL1F1_metamark_A" rend="allcaps">A</metamark>
                            <l n="2">Of man, the master, and the boy, these pictures doe unfold:</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="BB">
                            <l n="3">Wherein is bravely painted forth, A natural Irish grace</l>
                            <l n="4">Whose like in ev’ry point to view, hath seldom stepped in place.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="CC">
                            <l n="5">Mark me the <orgName corresp="#Woodkern"><hi rend="roman">kern</hi></orgName> that grips the axe, fast with his murd’ring hand,</l>
                            <l n="6">Then shall you say a righter knave, came never in the land:</l>
                        </lg>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div type="middleMargin">
                        <metamark place="middleMargin" function="plateID" corresp="#PL1F1_plateMark" rend="allcaps">1</metamark> <note type="clarification">Number “1” next to the column identifies this as plate 1.</note>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div type="column" n="2" corresp="#PL1F1_column2">
                        <cb n="2"/>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="DD">
                            <l n="7">As for the rest so trimly dressed, I speak of them no evil,</l>
                            <l n="8">In each respect, they are detect, (as honest as the devil.)</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="EE">
                            <l n="9">As honest as the <seg rend="roman"><rs>Pope</rs></seg> himself, in all their outward actions,</l>
                            <l n="10">And constant like the wavering wind, in their Imaginations,</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="FF">
                            <l n="11">Which may be prov’ed in sundry parts, hereafter that ensue,</l>
                            <l n="12">A perfect sign for to define, th’above additions true.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <span from="#PL1F1_capA_text"/>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
